HEADWORD: Insanable
<hw>In*san"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>insanabilis</ets>; cf. OF. <ets>insanable</ets>. See <er>In-</er>
not, and <er>Sanable</er>.]</ety> <def>Not capable of being healed;
incurable; irremediable.</def>⟦br⟧
